title: Grateful Dead Live at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium on 1993-06-26
lineage: AMS ST250 (FOB,DFC,ORTF) > AMS Control Box > Modified Sony D10 Pro > Modified Sony D10 > Sony D8 (master) > M-Audio Auiophile USB > Soundforge v 7.0 > CD Wave > FLAC16
description: Feel Like A Stranger, Brown Eyed Women, Spoonful, Lazy River Road, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song, Picasso Moon Iko Iko, Way To Go Home, Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> The Days Between-> Throwing Stones-> One More Saturday Night, E: Liberty

reviews.review_text:
2nd Half Comeback I give it 4 stars due to the boys saving the show by coming to life after intermission. Show started with a strong Stranger but just sort of plodded along. Iko-Iko started things rollin' and Vince sounded excellent on this version of Way to Go Home; singing in tune! Extended length Space was out there--Dan Healey partly responsible for the spacey beginning, me thinks. Strong Liberty. Bobby soldiered thru with a real raspy sounding throat.
The sound quality was so-so, sort of a muffled metallic sheen to some of the vocals, in particular. And a ghostly Stadium Echo that sounded like the audience was singing along, more than they were, from another dimension.
- Awesome show, as with so many in this tour.
